            <div class="small-12 columns">
                <div class="social-media-links UA_ShareModalLinks" style="text-align: left;">
                    <a href="mailto:?&amp;subject=From%20MDPI%3A%20%22Simulated%20Adversarial%20Attacks%20on%20Traffic%20Sign%20Recognition%20of%20Autonomous%20Vehicles&quot;&amp;body=https://www.mdpi.com/3287268%3A%0A%0ASimulated%20Adversarial%20Attacks%20on%20Traffic%20Sign%20Recognition%20of%20Autonomous%20Vehicles

With%20the%20development%20and%20application%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20%28AI%29%20technology%2C%20autonomous%20driving%20systems%20are%20gradually%20being%20applied%20on%20the%20road.%20However%2C%20people%20still%20have%20requirements%20for%20the%20safety%20and%20reliability%20of%20unmanned%20vehicles.%20Autonomous%20driving%20systems%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20unmanned%20vehicles%20also%20have%20to%20respond%20to%20information%20security%20attacks.%20If%20they%20cannot%20defend%20against%20such%20attacks%2C%20traffic%20accidents%20might%20be%20caused%2C%20leaving%20passengers%20exposed%20to%20risks.%20Therefore%2C%20we%20investigated%20adversarial%20attacks%20on%20the%20traffic%20sign%20recognition%20of%20autonomous%20vehicles%20in%20this%20study.%20We%20used%20You%20Look%20Only%20Once%20%28YOLO%29%20to%20build%20a%20machine%20learning%20model%20for%20traffic%20sign%20recognition%20and%20simulated%20attacks%20on%20traffic%20signs.%20The%20simulated%20attacks%20included%20LED%20light%20strobes%2C%20color-light%20flash%2C%20and%20Gaussian%20noise.%20Regarding%20LED%20strobes%20and%20color-light%20flash%2C%20translucent%20images%20were%20used%20to%20overlay%20the%20original%20traffic%20sign%20images%20to%20simulate%20corresponding%20attack%20scenarios.%20In%20the%20Gaussian%20noise%20attack%2C%20Python%203.11.10%20was%20used%20to%20add%20noise%20to%20the%20original%20image.%20Different%20attack%20methods%20interfered%20with%20the%20original%20machine%20learning%20model%20to%20a%20certain%20extent%2C%20hindering%20autonomous%20vehicles%20from%20recognizing%20traffic%20signs%20and%20detecting%20them%20accurately." title="Email">
                        <i class="fa fa-envelope-square" style="font-size: 30px;"></i>
                    </a>

                                        <a href="https://x.com/intent/tweet?text=Simulated+Adversarial+Attacks+on+Traffic+Sign+Recognition+of+Autonomous+Vehicles&amp;hashtags=mdpiengproc&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mdpi.com%2F3287268&amp;via=MDPIOpenAccess" onclick="windowOpen(this.href,600,800); return false" title="Twitter" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
